&gt;&gt; Perovskia atriplicifolia or Russian sage.

2
00:00:05,474 --> 00:00:09,015
This is a beautiful low growing shrub,

3
00:00:09,015 --> 00:00:11,235
18-24 inches,

4
00:00:11,234 --> 00:00:15,914
which moves and creates a clump with underground stems.

5
00:00:15,914 --> 00:00:19,649
It's gray foliage is distinctive in the landscape.

6
00:00:19,649 --> 00:00:22,919
Into July, August,

7
00:00:22,920 --> 00:00:24,255
and September, it puts up

8
00:00:24,254 --> 00:00:26,939
beautiful purple spikes of

9
00:00:26,940 --> 00:00:30,855
flowers which persist for two or more months.

10
00:00:30,855 --> 00:00:35,698
Perovskia has highly dissected leaves,

11
